Here are both approaches using Shell navigation and `IQueryAttributable`.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView `SelectionChanged`):

```csharp
// Approach A â€” string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B â€” pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive data in the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A â€” string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B â€” complex object arrives as-is
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire BindingContext** on the target page:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailsViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    <!-- or inject via DI in code-behind -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key differences:**

| | String query param | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | `$"route?key={val}"` | `new ShellNavigationQueryParameters { ... }` |
| **Data type** | Strings only | Any object |
| **Serialization** | URL-encoded | Passed by reference, not serialized |
| **Use case** | Simple IDs, flags | Full model objects |

Both approaches deliver data to the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method â€” you can even combine them in one navigation call by adding query-string params to the route *and* passing a `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` dictionary. Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
